\par }{\fs28\insrsid1715694\charrsid15666328 -}{\fs28\insrsid337484\charrsid15666328 This colostomy is created by bringing a loop of bowel through an incision in the abdominal wall. 
\par }{\fs28\insrsid1715694\charrsid15666328 -}{\fs28\insrsid337484\charrsid15666328 The loop is held in place outside the abdomen by a plastic rod slipped beneath it. 
\par }{\fs28\insrsid1715694\charrsid15666328 -}{\fs28\insrsid337484\charrsid15666328 An incision is made in the loop to allow the passage of stool through the loop colostomy.
\par  }{\fs28\insrsid1715694\charrsid15666328 -}{\fs28\insrsid337484\charrsid15666328 The supporting rod is removed approximately 7-10 days after surgery, when healing has occurred that will prevent the loop of bowel from retracting into the abdomen.
