(dysfunctional part)
\par }{\fs28\insrsid1715694\charrsid15666328 -}{\fs28\insrsid337484\charrsid15666328 
The functioning end of the intestine (the section of bowel that remains connected to the upper gastrointestinal tract) is brought out onto the surface of the abdomen, forming the stoma by
 cuffing the intestine back on itself and suturing the end to the skin.
\par }{\fs28\insrsid1715694\charrsid15666328 -}{\fs28\insrsid337484\charrsid15666328 The surface of the stoma is actually the lining of the intestine, usually appearing moist and pink.
\par }{\fs28\insrsid1715694\charrsid15666328 -}{\fs28\insrsid337484\charrsid15666328 An end colostomy is usually a permanent ostomy, resulting from trauma, cancer or another pathological condition
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\keepn\nowidctlpar\intbl\faauto\rin0\lin0\pararsid11951381\yts15 {\b\fs28\ul\cf17\kerning36\insrsid3670290\charrsid15666328 
\par }{\b\fs28\ul\cf17\kerning36\insrsid4468810\charrsid15666328 Continued care of colostomy after discharge}{\b\fs28\ul\cf17\kerning36\insrsid11951381\charrsid15666328 
\par }{\b\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid4468810\charrsid15666328 1.}{\b\fs28\ul\cf17\kerning36\insrsid4468810\charrsid15666328 Skin care}{\b\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid4468810\charrsid15666328 
\par }{\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid15023812\charrsid15666328 -Frequent Cleaning of the area around the stoma with soap and water and adequate drying.}{\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid4468810\charrsid15666328 
\par }{\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid15023812\charrsid15666328 -The skin around the stoma may be protected by application of water repellants as zinc oxide and Vaseline.
\par -To make sure that the colostomy bag fits snugly around the stoma to avoid leakage to the surrounding skin
\par }{\b\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid15023812\charrsid15666328 2.}{\b\fs28\ul\cf17\kerning36\insrsid15023812\charrsid15666328 Control of odor
\par }{\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid15023812\charrsid15666328 -Well managed colostomy should not have disturbing odor. This should be achieved by.
\par -Prompt changing of the colostomy bags to avoid filling with effluent and leakage.
\par -Avoid diet with spices causes\rquote  bad odor.
\par -Cleaning the skin around the stoma
\par }{\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid1324948\charrsid15666328 -G}{\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid15023812\charrsid15666328 eneral hygiene of the body
\par -Use of deodorants incase all this fails.
\par }{\b\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid15023812\charrsid15666328 3}{\b\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid4468810\charrsid15666328 .Diet
\par }{\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid1324948\charrsid15666328 -}{\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid4468810\charrsid15666328 Patient is encouraged to take a }{\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid15023812\charrsid15666328 balanced}{
\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid4468810\charrsid15666328  diet and to increase his fluid intake because of loss of water through the effluents.
\par }{\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid1324948\charrsid15666328 -}{\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid4468810\charrsid15666328 Avoid spices in food which give the effluents bad smell.
\par }{\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid1324948\charrsid15666328 -}{\fs28\cf17\kerning36\insrsid4468810\charrsid15666328 Avoid food with lots of roughage as vegetables which increases the amounts of effluent discharged.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\pararsid3024113\yts15 {\b\fs28\insrsid3024113\charrsid15666328 4}{\b\fs28\ul\insrsid3024113\charrsid15666328 .}{\b\fs28\ul\insrsid10055121\charrsid15666328 Lifestyle}{
